The project uses OpenZeppelin contracts via node_modules. The SafeCast.sol is from OZ v5.x (since the import in PriceManager.sol uses `@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/math/SafeCast.sol`).

In OpenZeppelin's SafeCast.sol (v5.x), `toUint256(int256 value)` is:
```solidity
function toUint256(int256 value) internal pure returns (uint256) {
    if (value < 0) {
        revert SafeCastOverflowedIntToUint(value);
    }
    return uint256(value);
}
```

This confirms that the function DOES revert on negative values. The property assertion is that this function reverts on negative price values, which is correct behavior. Now I should check the package.json to verify the exact OpenZeppelin version being used.

